Troubleshooting Tips
SpiderFoot Issues:

If modules fail, check API keys in configuration
Ensure Python dependencies are fully installed
Verify network connectivity for external queries
recon-ng Problems:

Run marketplace refresh if modules won't install
Check workspace permissions in ~/.recon-ng
Verify module compatibility with current version
Script Errors:

Ensure all paths point to correct tool installations
Check Python version compatibility (3.8+)
Verify subprocess commands work manually first
Network Issues:

Some OSINT queries may be rate-limited
Use delays between requests to avoid blocking
Consider using VPN if certain services are restricted
